    priceNum: 2428658, price: "$2,428,658", priceOriginal: "฿80,000,000", priceCurrency: "THB",
    added: 1, ownership: "Freehold",
    blurb: "Villa Beryl is a contemporary three-level sea-view residence built into a sloping hillside above Koh Samui's tranquil south coast at Thong Krut. Three en-suite bedrooms and a fully self-contained studio frame an open-plan white living space that opens to a 90 m² infinity pool, an outdoor bar and dining terrace, and uninterrupted views of the surrounding islands. 1,220 m² of build on a 1,800 m² plot — freehold, Chanote, move-in ready.",
    detail: "Villas built along a slope, such as this one, can yield something quite unique. Where a typical home places its public spaces on the ground floor with private rooms above, a home built into a hillside can invert that logic — putting the living areas at the top, where the entry is, and letting the bedrooms step down with the land. Villa Beryl sits on a sloping 1,800 m² plot above Thong Krut on Koh Samui's south coast, with three bedrooms — each with its own closets, bathroom and terrace — plus a fully contained studio with its own kitchen and living room, a main kitchen and living room, a pool, an outdoor bar and dining area, and parking for two cars. In total the structure delivers 1,220 m² across three levels, each adjusting to the topography.\n\nThe architecture is defined by a play of horizontal lines, formed by various overlapping canopies. Skylights draw natural light deep into the plan and open the lower level's interior to the sky. There is a sense of luxury, ease and warmth suited to the Koh Samui lifestyle and climate. The kitchen and living room are open and spacious, finished in a stark white that amplifies the sense of space, with accents in neutral tones that play with contrast. These rooms open out to a terrace with the pool, and beyond, the view of the surrounding islands — creating an exquisite continuity and dialogue between interior and exterior.\n\nThe aesthetic combines the clean lines and muted palette of contemporary design with exotic accents of natural elements and local stones unearthed during excavation. With its distinct long overhangs and roof planes, the style balances glamour with a cosy feeling of home, while borrowing from local traditions with sensitivity to history, location and context. The 90 m² infinity pool appears to merge with the horizon, wrapped by sun terraces, an alfresco dining area and an outdoor bar made for tropical entertaining; a self-contained studio, dedicated maid's quarters and covered parking for two cars add everyday practicality, all within a secure gated estate.\n\nThong Krut is renowned for its tranquility, natural beauty and authentic island charm, offering a slower pace of life with easy access to quiet beaches, fine dining and island-hopping excursions, and a comfortable drive to Lamai, Nathon and Samui International Airport. Offered freehold under Chanote title, fully furnished and move-in ready.",
