    mapQuery: "9.429406,99.965195",
    market: "Koh Samui",
    title: "Cantilevered Hilltop Villa with Floating Marble Infinity Pool, Cinema & 270° Sea Views",
    type: "Villa", view: ["Sea View", "Mountain View"], status: "Move-In Ready",
    beds: 5, baths: 5, interior: "2,000 m²", plot: "8,000 m²", year: null,
    priceNum: 3642987, price: "$3,642,987", priceOriginal: "฿120,000,000", priceCurrency: "THB",
    added: 1, ownership: "Freehold",
    blurb: "An extraordinary five-bedroom residence perched atop a steep hill within a private gated estate of around fifty lots above Koh Samui's south coast. Steel, glass and stone wrap a hilltop lookout where a white-marble infinity pool floats out over the jungle, framing uninterrupted 270° views across the southern coastline, the islands of Koh Taen and Koh Madsum, and the mainland beyond. A 250 m² King Suite wing, a 200 m² private cinema and games room, a sea-view gym and 4.5 rai of landscaped gardens complete a true trophy home. Freehold, Chanote title.",
    detail: "Perched high atop a steep hill within a private gated community of about fifty estate-sized lots above Koh Samui's southern coast, this is one of the island's genuine architectural statements. Sweeping mountain and ocean views pour in through floor-to-ceiling glazing throughout a house that wraps around its hilltop lookout, balancing steel, glass and stone with warm curves and sumptuous furnishing. An expansive promenade deck and a white-marble infinity pool reach out over the gardens, delivering uninterrupted 270° views across the southern coast, the neighbouring islands of Koh Taen and Koh Madsum, and the mainland. Surfaced in cool Balinese White stone, the deck holds carefully placed shaded seating, a fully tiled poolside bathroom and a well-equipped bar — the perfect stage for entertaining above the sea. All through the home, open spaces frame the surrounding 4.5 rai of landscaped gardens, where indigenous palms, lilies and bougainvillea nestle amongst large rocks hewn from the hillside.\n\nSecured in its own wing, the 250 m² King Suite floats above the hillside and backs onto a secluded walled garden. Italian white-marble flooring flows through four large rooms; the main bedroom rises to 4-metre coffered ceilings with a sunken bed area set behind 8 metres of glazing that bathes in natural light and sea views. A sunken lounge opens onto natural rock steps leading down to the walled lawn and its bougainvillea beds, while a designer bathroom with German fixtures and a walk-in dressing room in smoked-glass Italian furniture flank the central space. The wing also holds a fully equipped sea-view gym and direct access to the private 200 m² cinema and games room — 5-metre ceilings, acoustic insulation and antique teak floors, with a sunken lower level for table tennis and snooker, three reclining leather sofas facing a big screen, a bar and a connection to the courtyard garden.\n\nThe main house is entered through a serene courtyard from the double garage, opening to a double-height foyer where dramatic front glazing reveals the infinity pool and the sea and mountains beyond. A spiral glass stairway descends to three further guest bedrooms, each with stunning views and a covered balcony. Adjacent to the foyer, the Queen Suite carries coffered ceilings and a terrazzo-and-rosewood floor, leading to a remarkable glass-and-steel bathroom cube glazed on three sides and cantilevered six metres above the ground — an unforgettable spot to watch the sunset from the freestanding bath. The central lounge opens completely through bi-folding doors onto the promenade deck and pool, with deep coffered ceilings, terrazzo floors and a marble back wall backing onto a fully equipped teak-furnished kitchen. The whole house is fitted with bespoke LED lighting, silent air-conditioning and an exacting attention to detail in Italian marble, teak and terrazzo throughout.\n\nOffered freehold under Chanote title — 2,000 m² of build on an 8,000 m² plot, five bedrooms and five bathrooms. Priced at ฿120,000,000.",
