    blurb: "A near-two-rai hilltop plot at the top of one of Koh Samui's most original hillside communities — almost 2,883 m² with Chanote title, road access and a stunning panorama over the coastline and islands. The land faces south and west for the sunset, with high privacy yet good neighbours and easy convenience.",
    detail: "This land sits at the very top of Santikhiri, one of Koh Samui's most original and spectacular residential communities — a magical retreat to escape the stress of modern life. It is a village surrounded by nature, offering a high degree of privacy while keeping convenience, good care and good neighbours close at hand.\n\nThe plot measures 1-3-20.8 rai — almost two rai, around 2,883 m² — and is held under Chanote title, the strongest form of land ownership in Thailand, available freehold or on a leasehold basis. It connects directly to the community road and sits close to the common area, with a gentle elevated position that opens to a stunning panorama across the sea, the long beach below and the scattered islands beyond.\n\nThe land faces south and west, framing the sunset and catching cooling afternoon light and breeze — an ideal orientation for a private villa designed around the view. Surrounded by jungle and rock outcrops, it offers the seclusion of a hilltop while remaining part of an established, well-cared-for community of architectural villas.",
