    blurb: "A rare beachfront estate on the quiet south coast — contemporary Balinese pavilions on a wide 24-metre stretch of sand, a 21-metre pool running parallel to the shore, and daily golden sunsets over the islands of Koh Tan and Koh Madsum. Six suites, freehold, turnkey.",
    detail: "This beachfront Balinese luxury villa in Laem Sor is a rare opportunity to own a prime freehold, Chanote-title estate directly on the sand. Around 1,200 m² of built area is arranged across sea-facing pavilions to maximize privacy, comfort and panoramic ocean views, with a wide 24-metre beachfront that turns the daily golden sunset over Koh Tan and Koh Madsum into a defining feature of the home.\n\nAt its heart is a grand open-plan living pavilion embodying tropical resort-style living — expansive lounge and dining areas flowing through sliding walls to the pool terrace and the beach beyond. A 21-metre private saltwater pool runs parallel to the shoreline, drawing a striking line between the water, the white sand and the islands on the horizon, ideal for relaxed family living and large-scale entertaining.\n\nSix beautifully appointed bedrooms each connect to gardens or sea, served by seven bathrooms and guest powder rooms, with natural stone, rich timber and contemporary Balinese detailing throughout, single-storey and fully furnished. Laem Sor is among Koh Samui's most unspoiled coastlines yet close to restaurants (five minutes), Thong Krut village and island-hopping to Koh Tan (ten minutes), with Lamai about twenty minutes and the airport around thirty-five — a private boutique-resort feel with strong rental-investment fundamentals.",
