    blurb: "A glass house by celebrated Thai studio A49 that appears to float above the Chaweng Noi hillside — Balau-wood ceilings and decks, B&B Italia interiors, a 17-metre infinity pool over the bay, plus a basement entertainment den, spa, sauna and Technogym gym.",
    detail: "Live like a debonair Bruce Wayne in this stunning example of tropical modernist architecture, designed by celebrated Thai studio A49. Spanning 2,800 m² across four stepped levels, the glass house appears to float above the hill slopes, its ceilings and decking clad in local Balau wood as a nod to the tropical context, with a 17-metre infinity pool facing Chaweng Noi Beach and panoramic views of white sand, crystal water and distant islands. Named for the coconut (kelapa) trees around it, it blends into spectacular surroundings.\n\nThe living and dining areas are tastefully furnished with B&B Italia, Poltrona Frau and other designer brands, opening to an outdoor dining area and kitchen for barbecues by a private chef, with Alfred-like butler service throughout. Below, an entertainment den, a media room, a spa with Sunlighten sauna and steam room, and a private gym fitted with Technogym equipment connect to a sleek nomad-friendly workspace with high-speed internet.\n\nFour spacious bedrooms each have an en-suite and floor-to-ceiling glazing onto the view, arranged across the lower floors with the infinity pool, dining and living on the entry level. Fully staffed with a villa manager, private chef and gardener, with daily breakfast, a welcome fruit basket and a curated wine list, minutes from Chaweng's beaches, restaurants and nightlife.",
