    nightlyNum: 645, nightly: "$645", note: "Two staff & breakfast included", sleeps: "up to 8 guests · 2–3 bedrooms",
    blurb: "A serene single-storey beachfront villa composed as three minimalist pavilions on the golden sand of Laem Noi, Bang Por — set in a hidden bay beside the Four Seasons and the season-three White Lotus filming site, with a 14-metre saltwater infinity pool over the sea.",
    detail: "Nestled in a hidden bay on Koh Samui's quiet north shore — right next to the filming site of The White Lotus season three and the Four Seasons Resort — this elegant modern villa is secreted away from the hustle yet close to nearby amenities. The striking single-floor property is composed as three separate pavilions, comfortably accommodating up to six adults and a child across its three bedrooms, surrounded by lush tropical forest and rustling palms with breathtaking views of a neighbouring island.\n\nContemporary design keeps simplicity at its core: an open living area flows to an indoor dining space and open kitchen, opening out to a sun deck, an outdoor dining area with BBQ, and a seating area by the pool. The 14-metre salt-water infinity pool is ringed by eight sun-loungers with a shallow kid-friendly end, set right on the soft, tranquil sands of Laem Noi Beach — step straight from the deck to the sea, or take the two-person kayak out along the coast toward Nikki Beach and the Four Seasons.\n\nThe villa sits within a small, secure estate of five beachside villas with a guarded entrance, 24-hour CCTV and safety deposit boxes. Each bedroom is en-suite and air-conditioned, with a 75-inch Smart TV, sound system and high-speed WiFi throughout. Two staff are permanently on-site with daily breakfast included, and a private chef, yoga and tailored tours can be arranged on request.",
