    detail: "Raising the bar on the Bali villa experience, Akashi Residence is an architectural masterpiece that brilliantly strikes the balance between style and function. Located in quiet Pererenan, it offers an authentic slice of Bali without the big crowds — yet sits conveniently close to lively Canggu and the surf beaches of the island's west coast. Designed by renowned architect Alexis Dornier, this spectacular six-bedroom villa is perfect for groups of friends and extended families with kids of all ages.\n\nThe unique tropical design represents open-air living at its finest, with air-conditioned comfort whenever you need it. The central atrium is the social hub of the villa, its centrepiece a silver sculptural water slide that splashes into the swimming pool below. An abundance of living and entertainment spaces spreads over three levels, with each air-conditioned en-suite bedroom furnished with a king bed or two queens.\n\nBeyond the headline slide, the villa is a wellness haven and entertainer's dream: a TV and media room with an 85-inch Smart TV, a pool table, a private gym, an ice bath, a yoga deck, a roofed poolside lounge, and two dining rooms with adjoining kitchens. A 17-metre pool, daily breakfast, private chef and full villa team round out a stay that has been featured by Australian Traveller, Lifestyle Asia and Tatler Asia.",
